    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Description\n\nRunning LspRestart with any LSP name (e.g. `LspRestart lua_ls`) fails with the following error:\n```\nError executing Lua callback: /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:388: name: expected non\n-wildcard string, got nil                                                                    \nstack traceback:                                                                             \n        [C]: in function 'error'                                                             \n        vim/shared.lua: in function 'validate'                                               \n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:388: in function 'validate_config_name'      \n        /usr/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp.lua:408: in function '__index'                   \n        ...ocal/share/nvim/lazy/nvim-lspconfig/plugin/lspconfig.lua:136: in function <...ocal\n/share/nvim/lazy/nvim-lspconfig/plugin/lspconfig.lua:126> \n```\n\nPoking around, it seems to only happen since this commit - https://github.com/neovim/nvim-lspconfig/commit/0d90bb9bfb8e8b6b64f4a19b7dd3619f5d2788b5\n\nFrom a quick look, each client is now expected to be a table, but when passing names into the function, each client will be a string. This breaks everywhere that uses `client.name`, which is now nil.",
